<br>
You will need to equip the things you have.  Push the &quot;I&quot; key and bring up the Inventory window.  Take something from your inventory slots and drop it into the window in the center of the Inventory window.  It should auto-equip it to the right slot surrounding the window.  <br>
<br>
Also, get some bags/backback/boxes.  These are containers and you can right click on them and open them.  You can then put things in the containors. <br>
<br>
Every class has a Guild.  You had a rolled up note when your character started. Right click on this and it should tell you who to give it to.  If you hand it in, you should get a robe.  Additionally, in the Guild, there will be vendors who will sell you skills.  <br>
<br>
In the guild area, there should be someone who will give you some low level armor quests.  You will have to search around and /h to hail them.  Then any text in [brackets] should be used in a sentence back to the npc.  They will then give more information for the quests.  <br>
<br>
For the selling problem, some items you loot are No Drop.  You can sell or drop these items.  You can only turn them in to the NPC for that quest.  Chances are all of your inventory is not No Drop and can't be sold.  Get some bags and use these.  <br>
<br>
Help this helps.  <br>
