I'm sure youve noticed by now, when you zone into felwithe from Greater Faydark you can go right or left (or into a building) either way will take you around some winding passages.  Keep heading in the direction you would have if the building hadnt been in your way, and you will come to a pond.  Turn left and follow the walkway along the pond, and you will pass the baitshop.  Keep going that way and you will zone into (I think) North Felwithe.  Take a left, and keep going you will come to a big lake with a building high over the center.  There is a ramp up to the building, and 3 portal stones inside the building.  If you target one of the NPC (non player characters) an press the letter H, you will Hail him.  He will respond with helpfull information.  Step on one of the &quot;glowing&quot; portal stones and you will be ported to one of the 3 other buildings on the other side of the lake.<br>
<br>
One of those buildings will have your mage spells, and a trainer.  Remember to hail them, and right click on them.  You are probably using a dagger at this point, and might want to increase your piercing skills with your guild trainer.  You also want to find the vendor selling spells for your appropriate level.<br>
<br>
If you wish to see what your spells do before spending money on them, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/">Casters Realm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is a nice starting place.  Their information is not always correct, but its an excellent starting place.  This will take you directly to your <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Magician">Spell listing for magicians</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
One last thing, before you attack any creature click on it and press the C button to con (consider) it.  Or you can right click on it to do the same thing.  The colors will give you an indication of its difficulty.  In the future you will also use the message to tell you how your faction standing with them is.  (you should be ally to your hometown merchants for instance).<br>
<br>
Good hunting, and enjoy!!<br>
Flaamwing<br>
